Set a maximum lag order and look into the IC to select the AR(p) model

aic = NULL
bic = NULL
for (i in 0:8){
  tmp = arima(spread.est$dspread,c(i,0,0))
  tmpaic = AIC(tmp)
  tmpbic = BIC(tmp)
  aic = append(aic,tmpaic)
  bic = append(bic,tmpbic)
}

print(paste0("AIC Select Order of ",which(aic==min(aic))-1))
## [1] "AIC Select Order of 8"
print(paste0("BIC Select Order of ",which(bic==min(bic))-1))
## [1] "BIC Select Order of 2"

visualize AIC BIC

par(mfcol=c(2,1),mar = c(2,3,3,3))

plot(aic-min(aic)~seq(0,length(aic)-1),type='h',
     xlab="",
     ylab="",main='AIC')
lines(seq(0,length(aic)-1),aic-min(aic),lty=2)

plot(bic-min(bic)~seq(0,length(bic)-1),type='h',
     xlab="",
     ylab="",main='BIC')
lines(seq(0,length(bic)-1),bic-min(bic),lty=2)

fit ARIMA model

# test acf and pacf
acf(spread.est$dspread,12)

pacf(spread.est$dspread,12)

# use aic to select model
all.model = NULL
for (p in 0:2){
  for (q in 0:8){
    aic = arima(spread.est$dspread,order = c(p,0,q))$aic
    bic = BIC(arima(spread.est$dspread,order = c(p,0,q)))
    model = c(p,q,aic,bic)
    all.model=rbind(all.model,model)
  }
}
all.model = as.data.frame(all.model)
colnames(all.model)=c("p","q","aic",'bic')
head(all.model)

## for AR(8) model
all.ar.pred = NULL
for (i in 1:6){
  ar.model = arima(spread$T10Y3MM[1:444+i-1],order = c(8,1,0))
  ar.pred = predict(ar.model, 1)
  all.ar.pred = rbind(all.ar.pred, ar.pred)
}

we can observe a upwards trend and seasonality of period 12

retail = retail %>% arrange(date) %>% mutate(dsales = sales-dplyr::lag(sales,1)) %>%

ACF PACF

acf(retail$dsales)

# The difference has strong seasonal patterns. 
# The autocorrelations are large at lags which are multiples of the periodicity 12.

Take a seasonal difference of Δxt to handle the strong seasonal pattern. Δxt−Δxt−12

retail = retail %>% mutate(sdsales = dsales-dplyr::lag(dsales,12)) %>% na.omit()

take an initial guess and use ic

all.model2 = NULL
for (p in 1:3){
  for (q in 0:1){
    for (P in 1:2){
      for (Q in 0:1){
        print(c(p,q,P,Q))
        aic = arima(tmpdata,order=c(p,0,q),
                    seasonal=list(order=c(P,0,Q),period=12))$aic
        bic = BIC(arima(tmpdata,order=c(p,0,q),
                    seasonal=list(order=c(P,0,Q),period=12)))
        model = c(p,q,P,Q,aic,bic)
        all.model2=rbind(all.model2,model)
       
      }
        
    }
  }
}

sales.f = retail[1:284,]
sales.f = retail %>% 
  mutate(pred = sales,
         up = sales,
         bt = sales)
sales.f$pred[276:284]=pred
sales.f$up[276:284]=pred+2*se
sales.f$bt[276:284]=pred-2*se
sales.f = sales.f[240:nrow(sales.f),]

yr = range(sales.f[,c("sales","up","bt")])
plot(sales.f$pred~sales.f$date,type='l',col='red',ylim=yr)

lines(sales.f$bt~sales.f$date,lty=2)
